Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.81,0:00:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,finishing Transcending the Levels of Consciousness. Each of these levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.93,0:01:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,people say, well why don't people just move ahead? And it has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.96,0:01:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,ingrained attitudes which arise out of your animal nature, and these come in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.18,0:01:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,pairs. Generally they come in pairs, not in opposites, but in pairs. Each level has
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.30,0:01:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,its attraction and its aversion. So in this book I'm finishing, I take each
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.66,0:01:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness, describe it, give correlations, etc., and then at the end a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.48,0:01:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,list, and this is one of the lists for instance, that the dualities of attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.79,0:01:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and aversion. So each level has its payoff. If it didn't have a payoff you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.14,0:01:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't stay there, and it has its aversions. There's that which you're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.51,0:01:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,attracted and therefore there's that which you fear or regret or don't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.39,0:01:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of. The primary
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.56,0:01:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the primary thing that holds people's evolution of consciousness, and frankly
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.22,0:02:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to evolve you only need to know one thing, the one thing, you don't need anything else,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.50,0:02:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is the juice and the satisfaction you get out of it. Nothing else. It's not the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.61,0:02:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,thing itself, because this capacity to juice something and get, juice it for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.53,0:02:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,gain, animal pleasure, that's what the amoeba does.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.05,0:02:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can attach this juicing to anything. So it's nothing out there because there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.24,0:02:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't anything out there. The value of everything that you see out there and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.74,0:02:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore desire is a projection. You glamorize it, make it attractive because
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.21,0:02:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you project that attractiveness. I mean I wouldn't even want it in my house, and you're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.97,0:02:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to kill somebody for it, you know what I mean, or vice versa. You're willing to kill for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.61,0:02:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wouldn't have the damn thing around. So obviously value is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.18,0:03:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,something you project out there. Alice Bailey described that in the book called
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.44,0:03:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamour, very excellent understanding there from the White Brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.20,0:03:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Specialness is something you project out there, doesn't exist within the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. Now you're willing to die for it, surrender to it, the glamour of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.58,0:03:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler, the fatherland, see Kyle, I mean it's all projected value. The guy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.00,0:03:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated about, I don't know, 90 or 120 or something, and you think he's the great
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.72,0:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,fuhrer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.16,0:03:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even come up to 200, right. Okay, so this, the attraction is to the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfaction. Now this satisfaction the ego feels guilty about, it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.74,0:03:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissistic ego satisfaction, so it tries to disguise it. But if you do an
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.06,0:03:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,inner honesty, spiritual inventory of yourself, you'll see that any negativity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.64,0:04:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting is because, any negativity that's bothering you, is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.92,0:04:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is a payoff to it. Therefore what you're attached to is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.14,0:04:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,irrelevant, because you're only addicted to one thing. You're only addicted to one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.77,0:04:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,thing, and what you do is you move that thing around to values, people, positions,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.87,0:04:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,titles, money, wealth, you get a payoff out of it. That's the only reason you hang on to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-pity, you say nobody want to feel self-pity, oh yeah? You tried doing therapy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.86,0:04:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with somebody who's stuck in martyrdom, being wronged,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.70,0:04:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they're right, self-pity, made uncomfortable. Should the whole world
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.60,0:04:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,change itself because you feel uncomfortable the way it is? I mean the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.08,0:04:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,egomania of it, you know, the narcissism of it, this is really great, you know. It
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.31,0:04:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,makes me uncomfortable. Well that's your problem, isn't it? It's your problem if the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.53,0:05:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,name God over the courthouse gives you a sleepless night, I mean, you know what I
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,mean? So what? So the narcissistic person seeks to change the world instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.50,0:05:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.40,0:05:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to change others, you just have to change yourself, and then you experience
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,others differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.66,0:05:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so that's responsibility. So the only thing you need to know then, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.07,0:05:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,say you're angry and now you feel guilty about anger, and then you started looking
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.71,0:05:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,at the anger. The anger is not really the problem, the problem is pride. Oh, why are
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.61,0:05:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you angry? Because your pride has been hurt. And what is it that you fear? You fear shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.13,0:05:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so you see how
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you just can undo it, if you see what is the source of satisfaction? What kind of a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.39,0:05:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,payoff is the ego getting for hanging on? Being the martyr, of course being right. Being
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.05,0:06:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,right is being, the competition in today's world is between being right and being martyr.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.29,0:06:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can be a martyr and be right and that makes it a double win. And you do that by
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.71,0:06:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,objecting blame, and you're, you know, the Marxist dualism, the Marxist duality, the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.67,0:06:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,duality of being right and being right has its own bond, it has its own bond, and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.69,0:06:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of perpetrator-victim, which is projected onto any situation in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.59,0:06:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere is a perpetrator-victim, everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.79,0:06:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you choose to project that out there, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.27,0:06:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can assume, being the martyr, oh, poor me, oh, poor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.72,0:06:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so you can jump the ego's grip on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.80,0:06:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's happened is you're addicted to that position.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.58,0:06:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're addicted to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.26,0:06:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That position is not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.04,0:06:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.88,0:06:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.32,0:06:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.14,0:06:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's addicted to it is the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.74,0:06:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We've spoken of the experiencer in previous lectures, and we'll come back to it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.96,0:06:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't just the ego itself and its whole structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.87,0:07:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego presents itself, like the amoeba, through its, like you might call an edge, that's the processor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.68,0:07:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The processor is the quality that's incredibly complex in one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.50,0:07:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It evaluates everything from multiple viewpoints, simultaneously, and distills out the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.22,0:07:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the edge of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.00,0:07:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the probe that came out of evolution, that the amoeba has to quickly decide what is edible, not edible, what's good for you, what's poisonous, enemy, quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.50,0:07:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to quickly process.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.90,0:07:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a processor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.18,0:07:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Very complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.82,0:07:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a complex processor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.76,0:07:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In one ten-thousandth of a second, it processes enormous, enormous banks of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.23,0:07:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No combination of computers could possibly do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.91,0:07:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just far too complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.81,0:08:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it includes value, meaning, significance, prioritization.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.89,0:08:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A computer can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.14,0:08:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't value things higher than one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.52,0:08:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got bits of information, and it doesn't reflect projected value.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.97,0:08:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer doesn't, you know, think more highly of this bit of information than it does of this information, but your ego does.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.35,0:08:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to discontinue from the experiencer is the inner way that requires intense discipline, and we cover that pretty much in the book Devotional Non-Duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.39,0:08:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.31,0:08:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.47,0:09:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way in which one seeks to disidentify with that aspect of the ego, which is not only in a dualistic positionality, but is the leading edge of the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.83,0:09:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, ultimately, what you're addicted to is experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.68,0:09:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans are hooked on experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.38,0:09:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you keep changing the channel, and then you turn on the music, then you go eat a bite of this and that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.26,0:09:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Addicted to experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.96,0:09:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because out of evolution, it was through experiencing that one survived, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.70,0:09:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty, then, the feedback, that which you're getting from this experiencer edge of the ego, is the readout of a tape monitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality, then, is the program out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.14,0:09:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets recorded on the tape, and now you're plugged into the tape monitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.05,0:09:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Experientially, what you're getting is the tape monitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.65,0:10:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not getting res externa, nature, reality, the world as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.16,0:10:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting the readout.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.82,0:10:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not even addicted to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.10,0:10:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.96,0:10:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh, I'm so hooked on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.74,0:10:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're not hooked on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.10,0:10:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hooked on this readout.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.42,0:10:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hooked on the readout that you're getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.38,0:10:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And this experiencer is reading out to you because it's processing based on poor prioritization.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.00,0:10:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you value, then, gets projected out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer aspect of the ego thinks this is important, and it gets attached to it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.26,0:10:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you get attached to the juice you get out of that perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.78,0:10:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.82,0:10:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way the ego keeps itself alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.52,0:10:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the ego has no source of spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.69,0:10:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It only has animal energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.59,0:11:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, out of every experience, it has to extract the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.49,0:11:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the source of animal existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.33,0:11:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have a source of energy within itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.26,0:11:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, the ego survives by virtue of taking glee at the suffering of others, being right, winning, gaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.84,0:11:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.07,0:11:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And he deserved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.27,0:11:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Take that, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.47,0:11:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Boom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.67,0:11:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, that makes you feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.67,0:11:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's done a lot of times, or a lot of lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.18,0:11:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, did he ever get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.18,0:11:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And he deserved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.89,0:11:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't believe in Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.09,0:11:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.25,0:11:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.99,0:11:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, did we do with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.49,0:11:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He did it for Allah, and I did it for Jesus, and we killed each other, snicker-snack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, he was good, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.22,0:12:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And every lifetime that I've had a challenge like that, we come up for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.92,0:12:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And got you again, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.52,0:12:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And he gets me at the same time, right through the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, we both go out of body, breaking and laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.12,0:12:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, did we do this one again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.52,0:12:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we did this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.56,0:12:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can even get you the date of it and the place of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.66,0:12:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the Crusades.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.26,0:12:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we have, what, quarter after?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.69,0:12:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.69,0:12:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you have an aversion and attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.69,0:12:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is based on how you perceive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.45,0:12:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And your perception, then, is the consequence of spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.25,0:12:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, aligning yourself with divinity, by whatever means, religion, spirituality,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.85,0:12:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or just commitment to truth and integrity in a secular way,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.85,0:12:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, does bring in kundalini energy, which now transforms the appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,significance, and meaning of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.74,0:12:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This kundalini energy, as it begins to flow, becomes quite strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.82,0:12:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.72,0:12:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At 540, which is unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.76,0:13:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, unconditional love is a practical goal in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.96,0:13:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what Jesus Christ and other religions really teach,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.16,0:13:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is try to reach unconditional love is practical goal in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.56,0:13:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can learn how to, you can learn that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.76,0:13:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you follow religious teachings, you will reach unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.18,0:13:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of 12-step groups, by the way, is 540, unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.98,0:13:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is reached by 0.4% of the human population, 0.4.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.38,0:13:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Every reach is 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.58,0:13:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, expecting the other nations are going to love you if you're nice to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.17,0:13:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the chances are zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.34,0:13:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.17,0:13:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they would have to be over 500 to even appreciate integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.60,0:13:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, anyway, 540 then releases kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.30,0:14:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The kundalini energy transforms brain physiology, changes how you see and experience life,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.00,0:14:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,changes your value and your goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.73,0:14:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjectively, it's experienced as an exquisite sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.94,0:14:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you've never heard about it, I've never heard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, it's exquisite sweetness flowing up your spine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.34,0:14:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Woo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.44,0:14:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And it flows into your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.34,0:14:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brain is like having a slow, forever orgasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.34,0:14:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's just incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.76,0:14:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better than an orgasm because it's got a quality that is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a quality, not a sensation, it's like.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.82,0:14:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, eventually, this energy begins to perform the miraculous,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.92,0:14:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the so-called siddhis, s-i-d-d-h-i-s, becomes spontaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.92,0:14:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're clairaudient. You're clairvoyant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.72,0:14:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see auras.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.02,0:14:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Distance viewing, healings, people come to you and you just hold them in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.84,0:14:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the miraculous appear before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.64,0:14:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no person doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all phenomena that are consequent to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.34,0:15:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And a good teacher warns you in advance when you finally reach this level
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.90,0:15:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's inevitable, a group like this, everybody's going to reach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.10,0:15:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When these phenomena begin to appear, you have to be aware they are not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.10,0:15:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't claim them as my powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.30,0:15:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you get hooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.00,0:15:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My powers, much less peddle them and sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.40,0:15:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you a class on how to, you know, levitate or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.67,0:15:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.72,0:15:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Those things happen spontaneously as a consequence of the power of the kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.52,0:15:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The world calls them miraculous and goes, ooh-la, ooh-la, ooh-la.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.18,0:15:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're careful not to parade them around and you try to conceal them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.88,0:15:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world will really tag you around, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.28,0:15:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The miraculous happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.58,0:15:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no performer of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.84,0:15:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There are famous gurus out there, don't calibrate all that high,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.54,0:15:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, as miracle workers, you know, they are the miracle, of course, are the miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.04,0:16:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not the source of the miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just a dumbbell that hasn't got enough power probably to lift the suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the miraculous is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.37,0:16:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And you witness, we witness, what we witness is the person,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see why they're having lunch with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.47,0:16:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then you get the unspoken question, then you see what the problem is,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.64,0:16:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then somebody says, well, she has this or that, and you say, oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.13,0:16:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then within yourself you feel the energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.73,0:16:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's that person's karmic propensity which will decide the consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.13,0:16:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The field is there and if the karmic propensity is there, the healing occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.59,0:16:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's not, if a person is really spiritually evolved,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.89,0:16:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,like the Course in Miracles, whether a healing occurs or not is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.51,0:16:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you reach that, whether a healing occurs is irrelevant,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.12,0:17:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you live or die is irrelevant, you have completed the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.92,0:17:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, to precipitate it, you get a person to the point that they lose their fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.50,0:17:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You lose their fear of death, you know, and I used to do it with patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, and then what, and then what, and then this will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.10,0:17:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So I used to turn to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.40,0:17:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what, and then this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.10,0:17:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you go through all your fears, you will always end up with the same fear at the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.80,0:17:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is the fear of death, and then I will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.28,0:17:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you say to them, so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.06,0:17:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Bang, and sometimes you'll see a patient gets it right then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.48,0:17:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Dying is inevitable anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.94,0:17:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a person is 100% fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.06,0:17:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Mortality rate for humanness is 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.61,0:17:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it happens now or later, what's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.41,0:18:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When you accept the inevitability of the inevitable, it's amazing how your fears disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.81,0:18:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, all right, so if I lose the job, screw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.14,0:18:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.34,0:18:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He came in terrified, he's going to lose the job and face the basis of all fears is fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.74,0:18:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you say, and then what, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.94,0:18:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll be lonely, then they won't hire me, then I'll run out of money, then I'll be homeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'll starve to death, so then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.30,0:18:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I'll die, so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.72,0:18:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the first time I said that to a patient, she said, and then what if it doesn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.30,0:18:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, then you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And she said, oh, because if you're coming from that, the higher space, and you say that, they'll get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.68,0:18:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not coming from a higher space, they would take that as an affront, you know, and frighten them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.74,0:18:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't tell that to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.74,0:18:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we got exactly where we're at.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.22,0:19:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we're doing it different today because Betty and Nico,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,have to leave, they have another spiritual event, and so we'll have Nico chant until lunchtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll reconvene this afternoon at what time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.50,0:19:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we reconvene then at two o'clock, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.65,0:19:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.89,0:19:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I have two words to say about death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.89,0:19:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.95,0:19:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.76,0:25:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Best use of this time and our time together.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.83,0:25:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So this year we're finishing up what I would call the didactic first couple of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.83,0:25:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We pretty much covered everything in power versus force, eye of the eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.44,0:25:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,our reality and subjectivity, truth versus falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.11,0:25:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we will complete the transcending laws of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.30,0:25:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and end up on devotional non-duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.86,0:25:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,at which point we will all just sit looking happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.92,0:25:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then next year I thought we will devote more, more, hardly any time,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.05,0:25:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to lectures or didactic material,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.21,0:26:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll make it more traditional discussion, question and answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.46,0:26:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean? Free discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.46,0:26:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We've become really a very unique spiritual group,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.49,0:26:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and as such we'll move more and more into group operation,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.97,0:26:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,where instead of didactic lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.10,0:26:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we have free open discussions and clarification,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.10,0:26:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and questions and discussion and answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.00,0:26:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and so forth with the group, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.32,0:26:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's got some name in Sanskrit, I forget what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.32,0:26:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Satsang?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.42,0:26:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.04,0:26:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Satsang.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.04,0:26:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well anyway, you have to speak Sanskrit to come to the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.94,0:26:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So next year we'll move more into questions and answers and free discussion,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.93,0:26:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because the group is now aware of all the basic material.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.99,0:26:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the basic material,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.47,0:26:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we've confirmed this before,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.72,0:27:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the chances of becoming enlightened are now one thousand times greater than in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.72,0:27:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One thousand times greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.88,0:27:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of the information and the evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.20,0:27:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,so as in the olden days it was an extreme rarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.94,0:27:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we expect to see it recur more and more often,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.32,0:27:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and to facilitate that transcending laws of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.32,0:27:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I address, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.32,0:27:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the levels around 850 and up,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.32,0:27:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which are very difficult to articulate,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.32,0:27:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and people say,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.45,0:27:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,why is he talking about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.45,0:27:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.45,0:27:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,some of you are going to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.45,0:27:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you hit the void,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.45,0:27:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's pretty stunning, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.45,0:27:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.52,0:27:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we discuss the downside of the pathway of negation, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.74,0:27:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which are really only necessary for very advanced students,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.74,0:27:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're already pretty advanced students,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.74,0:28:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we get that now is the time to be more informal
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.87,0:28:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and less didactic and more interactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.87,0:28:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The same material will come up,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.87,0:28:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but of course in a different context,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.87,0:28:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and very often a lot of people get more out of that spontaneous emergence
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.87,0:28:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of a subject rather than some kind of a linear presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.00,0:28:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we've done is,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.00,0:28:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in a very linear way,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.90,0:28:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we've done it in a non-linear way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.30,0:28:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's because you're starting out from ordinary minds, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.40,0:28:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you contextualize an ordinary mind
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.40,0:28:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,before you move on past ordinary minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.40,0:28:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to start out where the modern mind is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.40,0:28:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The modern mind is not into where it was a thousand years ago, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.76,0:28:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The modern mind has to be addressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.46,0:28:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.16,0:29:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing advanced spiritual mentioned is really addressed to the current mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.36,0:29:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore part of the purpose was to correlate modern mind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.36,0:29:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with advanced spiritual teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.68,0:29:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So how to jump that paradigm from the 400s into the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.68,0:29:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and then from the 500s on up,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.45,0:29:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which become progressively non-linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.95,0:29:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and at 600 is quite non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.08,0:29:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that, when you hit 600, you can leave if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.76,0:29:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Most do, you know, yeah, over 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.27,0:29:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When they get to that level, there's no need for the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.27,0:29:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just falls over, which is not too interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.63,0:30:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,However, depending on carrying propensities and obligations
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.63,0:30:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that you forgot now because you're back in the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.43,0:30:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but when you leave it, you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.63,0:30:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So then the world may come along and insist that you eat and poke you,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.23,0:30:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,force you to have a sandwich whether you like it or not, and stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.14,0:30:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't eaten since Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.74,0:30:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Friday, don't you think you ought to?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.38,0:30:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right, we're explaining all those phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.98,0:30:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,explaining those phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.78,0:30:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and how each one of them, as advanced as they can be,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.78,0:30:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,can also be transcended because, sooner or later,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.84,0:30:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a group like this is dedicated to enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.04,0:30:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,will reach the highest states.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.53,0:30:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the time to hear about the highest states is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.88,0:30:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.08,0:30:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, all by yourself in the middle of nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.28,0:30:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and no telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.94,0:31:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, but the knowingness is encased forever
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.75,0:31:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as a frequency and energy field within the aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.95,0:31:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.44,0:31:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Gloria in excelsis Deo.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.96,0:31:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Down through the ages forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.60,0:31:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The vibration and that frequency in the aura
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.31,0:31:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that you pick up from the highest truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.31,0:31:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we calibrated the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.31,0:31:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,will persist for at least 25 lifetimes or a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.11,0:31:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to worry for a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.71,0:31:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You already know what you need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.11,0:31:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the propitious moment out of silence and nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.91,0:31:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,comes the knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.67,0:31:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's no thinkingness, there's no memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.67,0:31:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you've learned is useless because the mind stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.20,0:31:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And now up comes a confrontation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.06,0:31:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point, a knowingness emerges of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.92,0:32:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk straight ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.32,0:32:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.68,0:32:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't just the thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.08,0:32:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the power of the thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.68,0:32:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the thought comes from somebody who's done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.68,0:32:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what gives it the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.36,0:32:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the reliance is on the strength
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.26,0:32:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of that truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.46,0:32:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And it better be convincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.46,0:32:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It better be convincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.59,0:32:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the obligation of the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.59,0:32:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we're done with him, we'll get on with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.79,0:32:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.17,0:32:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The confusion of love and passionate attachment,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.32,0:32:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which is in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.32,0:32:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And passionate attraction, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.00,0:32:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with all what Hollywood and the world makes of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.20,0:32:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you would think it was really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.60,0:32:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates at 145.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.60,0:32:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of a panting tomcat in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.98,0:33:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to say it, but it's a desire to make becomes very intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.88,0:33:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see the biologic evolution of the mammalian species.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.88,0:33:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for that, we wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.68,0:33:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're not putting it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.48,0:33:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason we're mentioning it is because there is an error in spiritual teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.54,0:33:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Also prevalent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.29,0:33:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one out of Sedona, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.96,0:33:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,which which says that love is an attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.34,0:33:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.74,0:33:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the one that blew that one girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.54,0:33:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is not an attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.67,0:33:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,See, passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.69,0:33:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This this year is an attachment and you're attached to desiring this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.75,0:33:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,glamorization of the desired object out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.80,0:33:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But love is a quality of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.60,0:34:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, negate the negate love.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.80,0:34:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll end up in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.40,0:34:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.97,0:34:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the attachment, the possessiveness, the craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.29,0:34:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not love.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.49,0:34:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.58,0:34:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Every you know, you can watch your own pets.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.58,0:34:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They got it on thing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.14,0:34:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what you have to let go of is the attachment to that desiring this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.94,0:34:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That specialness, the specialness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.20,0:34:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That object becomes very special.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.40,0:34:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't live without it and you must have it, seize it, desire it, possess it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.00,0:34:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're jealous of how somebody might flirt with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.20,0:34:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you'll kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.14,0:34:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.14,0:34:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you've all killed the former lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.16,0:34:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you didn't, what was the matter with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.76,0:34:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.68,0:34:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they deserve to die, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.72,0:34:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Poach on my territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.72,0:35:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Cost you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.43,0:35:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.23,0:35:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we made a way to differentiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.72,0:35:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what you're supposed to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.72,0:35:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This cravingness, this transitory excess sex hormone.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.55,0:35:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all very love sprained and very physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.83,0:35:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can tell it because it gets frantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.55,0:35:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like an addiction and a craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.75,0:35:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't get it, you're going to commit suicide or homicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.55,0:35:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to stalk them or something you have to possess.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.95,0:35:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.75,0:35:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,your life, the impact of this energy field that the world calls love is your life is disrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.38,0:35:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't sleep or eat, sort of a temporary madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.77,0:35:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're frustrated, you end up with depression, rage, hatred, blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.17,0:35:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, classically murder and suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.97,0:35:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Love, which is a quality of 500 and up, is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.17,0:35:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possessive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.37,0:35:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not controlling.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.97,0:36:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a spiritual state.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.57,0:36:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you uplifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.97,0:36:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel bonded.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.83,0:36:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you feel about that person is permanent.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.23,0:36:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It releases endorphins instead of adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.46,0:36:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings calm and balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.26,0:36:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life is enhanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.66,0:36:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more self-fulfilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.46,0:36:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel improved as a great well-being as a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.66,0:36:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to be with, you feel grateful to that person and your life is enhanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.88,0:36:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it comes about really through the right side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.68,0:36:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.08,0:36:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the consequence of the Kundalini energy which pours out at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.08,0:36:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is not to be negated.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.08,0:36:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you negate that, you will end up at nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.08,0:36:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the pathway of negation, you will end up in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.88,0:36:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not putting down the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.28,0:36:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.91,0:36:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Most impressive thing beyond imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.97,0:36:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.77,0:36:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.17,0:37:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.37,0:37:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's forever non-dimensional.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.77,0:37:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Has no beginning, no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.69,0:37:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody there, nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.09,0:37:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's intensely impressive and wondrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.41,0:37:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Had it not been for having experienced the presence as a teenager,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.63,0:37:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which was that of an infinite love that was just melting by the sheer force of its infinite power,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.03,0:37:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,there would have been the presumption again that this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.41,0:37:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if this is it, I wouldn't have gotten hit with it when I was age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.24,0:37:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothingness versus, allness versus nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.44,0:37:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, out of that lifetime, you ended up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.60,0:37:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.60,0:37:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So at age three, I get hit with it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.60,0:37:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the confrontation was, at age three, out of nothing, suddenly there was the awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.86,0:37:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence, not as me, just existence, period.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.28,0:38:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was not happy with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.85,0:38:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not at all happy to come out of the void, nothingness into existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.56,0:38:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly, the corollary came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.56,0:38:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you exist, therefore, it could have happened that you would not have existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.00,0:38:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha. Instantly came up the fear of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.16,0:38:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.23,0:38:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the reality existence versus nonexistence?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.23,0:38:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it allness or nothingness?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.23,0:38:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three, I didn't think about it, but I just totally got what the presentation was.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.90,0:38:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it took 38 years to resolve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.08,0:38:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that's where negation will take you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.36,0:38:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If negation, the void, was real, you couldn't emerge from it, nor would there be anyone to report it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.72,0:38:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.83,0:39:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What would be reporting the reality of a void?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.89,0:39:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which you consider you is also void.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.60,0:39:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's nothingness, then there's nothing to say there's nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.60,0:39:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the inner paradox itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.65,0:39:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.45,0:39:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three, I wouldn't know what you're talking about, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.67,0:39:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I only spoke Sanskrit in those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.67,0:39:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And ancient Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.67,0:39:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Ancient Greek, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.67,0:39:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.67,0:39:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the thing to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.67,0:39:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You have now heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.05,0:39:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here has got it in their aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.05,0:39:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here has it in their aura forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.05,0:39:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.40,0:39:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody here is going to get hung up on the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.24,0:39:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.92,0:39:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we share our experience, strength, and experience, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.15,0:39:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now we were talking about dualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.44,0:40:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the last time we started at the bottom of the scale, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.44,0:40:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We started at, what's at the bottom of the scale of consciousness, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.50,0:40:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.59,0:40:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, then we, oh, we're moving ahead out of shame today.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.71,0:40:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we would hit all these sets of dualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.71,0:40:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I have them at the end of the first chapters in Transcending Levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.71,0:40:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's holding each one is an attraction and aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.16,0:40:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one real attraction,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.16,0:40:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is to the payoff of your current position.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.32,0:40:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to disassemble that current position
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.32,0:40:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what it is you're getting out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.21,0:40:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you getting out of being the loser?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.21,0:40:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're getting to be the loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.21,0:40:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.21,0:40:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you getting out of being the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.21,0:40:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting to be the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.34,0:40:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim has got the biggest payoff in today's society,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.34,0:41:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,other than being right. Being right beats them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.24,0:41:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At the very bottom, actually, we had apathy, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.37,0:41:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't we have apathy? Or no, and apathy is coming next.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.37,0:41:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll just go with guilt and hate, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.85,0:41:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Without going to apathy, I won't care about guilt and hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.39,0:41:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to arouse myself to get up to guilt and hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.74,0:41:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction, of course, is judgmentalism towards yourself and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.74,0:41:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Judge not, says the Lord. Judge not.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.87,0:41:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, and when we recontextualize divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.87,0:41:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as though it was in a giant electromagnetic field,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.87,0:41:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're a little magnetic filing,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.09,0:41:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that sort of changes the way in which you experience guilt, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.09,0:41:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that the way you've been programmed led you to that,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.09,0:41:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore, out of what is really an intrinsic innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.89,0:42:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you chose that because you thought you were choosing the good at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.89,0:42:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the mind is like a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.34,0:42:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic hardware will play any program,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.34,0:42:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize the mind cannot defend itself against falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.34,0:42:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here, we're all sitting ducks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.85,0:42:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll play any software that gets programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.85,0:42:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How long does it take you to get programmed?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.85,0:42:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You just had it. You just got programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.23,0:42:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to do a slosh. M&M.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.28,0:42:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.02,0:42:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. Burned into your head is M&M.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.02,0:42:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest of your lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.72,0:42:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty years from now, you're in the North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.58,0:42:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You dig through the snow, and here's a dead Eskimo,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.58,0:42:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and in his pocket, he's got M&M.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.44,0:42:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty years later, you know what an M&M is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.44,0:43:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how long it took to program you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.44,0:43:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You just got programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.47,0:43:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how can you defend yourself against that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.47,0:43:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.47,0:43:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot defend yourself against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.92,0:43:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.91,0:43:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the victim of what your innocence has been programmed by.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.91,0:43:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is the victim by which their innocence has been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.90,0:43:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why fascism, totalitarianism, theocratic, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.76,0:43:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,seeks the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.88,0:43:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,First thing they do is try to program the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.88,0:43:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Get them into the youth movement, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.52,0:43:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Replace the authority of the parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.52,0:43:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Replace the teaching and the values of the state,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.32,0:43:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what you see in today's society,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.32,0:43:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which is becoming progressively totalitarian in the name of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.32,0:43:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The parent no longer has jurisdiction over their child.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.74,0:43:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The school does.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.74,0:44:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of a program that's been politically put into the school system.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.51,0:44:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not up to you to decide about sexual teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.51,0:44:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The state has taken over.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.51,0:44:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You want your five-year-old to know you're all about pedastry and oral sex
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.27,0:44:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and various perversions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.27,0:44:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How about S&M, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.27,0:44:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.27,0:44:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, freedom of speech, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.27,0:44:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Children should know about S&M, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.27,0:44:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,At age five or six.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.27,0:44:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, the ads, you know, you can hear a six-year-old say,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.27,0:44:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, why should you call a doctor after three hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.27,0:44:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, four hours or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.43,0:44:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Four hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.43,0:44:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, why should Daddy call a doctor after four hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.43,0:44:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She's just a toddler.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.71,0:44:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a toddler, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.71,0:44:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're supposed to explain it to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.71,0:44:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.71,0:44:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let somebody else do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.31,0:44:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's never too soon for them to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.37,0:44:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is really pretty dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.95,0:45:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.95,0:45:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt then, you want to punish yourself or others because you've been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.30,0:45:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other thing about guilt is you're refusing God's mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.30,0:45:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're justifying negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.30,0:45:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're rejecting your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.52,0:45:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rigid, narrow view.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.32,0:45:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It calls for penance, which is a self-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.42,0:45:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you ever think of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.28,0:45:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you realize all these demonstrations of penance?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.28,0:45:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even an egoistic self-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.44,0:45:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look how guilty I am and how sinful I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.44,0:45:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, give me a break, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.67,0:45:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, the sin of the century or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.67,0:45:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgot your mother-in-law's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.92,0:45:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't send her a birthday card.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.92,0:45:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how could I have done such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.94,0:45:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, the ego clings to this position.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.74,0:45:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This position of guilt reinforces it and enjoys its meanness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.93,0:46:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because now you project it and you have hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.93,0:46:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hate is then projected onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.06,0:46:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So guilt and hate go extremely well together.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.06,0:46:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of hating yourself, you project it into the world and you hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.44,0:46:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you've got to have a them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.44,0:46:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got to have somebody out there that you can blame it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.44,0:46:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.08,0:46:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator-victim model, which is a dualistic positionality,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.08,0:46:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of the distorted hermeneutics of relativistic epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.82,0:46:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Distorted hermeneutics of relativistic epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.82,0:46:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, there you've got the cue to what ails society today. Very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.01,0:46:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Distorted understanding of what is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.32,0:47:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to distorting meaning by denying that there is an absolute by which meaning can be discerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.39,0:47:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, all meaning is relativistic and, like Lewis Carroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.39,0:47:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a word means just what I want it to mean and neither more nor less.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.39,0:47:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is about age, what, five?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.39,0:47:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they teach in the university now, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.39,0:47:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Age five, kindergarten mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.39,0:47:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A word means just what I want it to mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.25,0:47:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing more or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.25,0:47:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, Joey.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.25,0:47:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You are now going to be a professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.25,0:47:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an academic requirement now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.67,0:47:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so that's the attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.67,0:47:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time there's an aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.63,0:47:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering judgment to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.63,0:47:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you don't have the capacity to judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.63,0:47:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Aversion is to forgiving yourself and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.11,0:47:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, look at all the opportunities people have
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.11,0:47:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to just forgive the other side and forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.11,0:47:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But they cling to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.91,0:47:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Accept mercy and compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.91,0:47:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender the secret pleasure you're getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.91,0:48:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an aversion to taking responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.91,0:48:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the reason this comes about is you don't choose essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.91,0:48:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going along with linear appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.91,0:48:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're refusing to be flexible and see both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.32,0:48:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is not of any service to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.32,0:48:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're reluctant to ask God for a miracle and recontextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.64,0:48:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.44,0:48:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really, when you ask for a miracle,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.99,0:48:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you're asking divinity in the form of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.99,0:48:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,present as the Holy Spirit to recontextualize it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.99,0:48:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,take you out of the fixation, the perceptual fixation you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.99,0:48:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the easy way. This seems like it could be hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.99,0:48:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hard to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.53,0:48:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, with flexibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.30,0:48:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find that it's easier to do in Rome as the Romans do.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.26,0:49:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find it's really a lot easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.26,0:49:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really hard to maintain a different culture in a different context.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.26,0:49:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But some people persist anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.58,0:49:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Cling to the old out of fear of the unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.58,0:49:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems easy, and it's hard or difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.84,0:49:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So people would rather ignore the negativity
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.84,0:49:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than get upset, look at it, or face it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.84,0:49:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the attraction, is the comfort of the familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.64,0:49:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the aversion is to looking at it, becoming different,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.64,0:49:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and, of course, to take responsibility and be accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.64,0:49:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,To take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.66,0:49:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I like Bill Cosby.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.76,0:49:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He's saying, you're not going to get out of where you are
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.76,0:49:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.95,0:49:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, he's getting hit for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.95,0:49:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know for what reason, but it seems to be a sensible teaching, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.95,0:49:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,To take responsibility for your action.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.95,0:49:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, you're not just passively,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.13,0:50:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,along yourself, to get run over by society.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.13,0:50:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When you stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.12,0:50:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these things here are only difficult because they're resisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.12,0:50:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,When you let go resisting it and look forward to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.35,0:50:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,now it doesn't take effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.35,0:50:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't take effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.35,0:50:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to see people as innocent,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.35,0:50:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what they do, becomes easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.15,0:50:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't upset you to look at or face a failing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.39,0:50:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, as we said, the human mind is programmed
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.15,0:50:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is easily misled.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.56,0:50:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of seeing other people as wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.76,0:50:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it's more comfortable, you'll find within yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.79,0:50:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to see them as misled.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.79,0:50:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They believe this because they were misled.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.14,0:50:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.17,0:50:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,For chronic reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.24,0:50:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,For reasons of the evolution of their consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.24,0:51:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people are misled.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.13,0:51:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They're misled by the ambiance of cultures
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.29,0:51:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which are very, very strong and long-standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.29,0:51:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And you would have to be already pretty evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.29,0:51:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to resist being programmed in that culture
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.29,0:51:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in which it reappears all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.74,0:51:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easier, the anticipated pleasure is to just ignore a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.74,0:51:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than get upset and look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.87,0:51:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The upset is due to resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.67,0:51:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easier to refuse to own it and blame it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.37,0:51:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,than it is to take that responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.37,0:51:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and be accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.37,0:51:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the biggest excuse of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.37,0:51:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,called, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.37,0:51:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't really change my ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.47,0:51:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been this way all my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.56,0:51:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was brought up that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.56,0:51:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse after excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.56,0:51:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if I say to somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.52,0:52:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,could you let go wanting to be that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.62,0:52:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.42,0:52:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.42,0:52:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I hold a loaded gun up to his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.58,0:52:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, if you can, I'm going to blow your brains out.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.58,0:52:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.58,0:52:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Your problem is you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.58,0:52:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.28,0:52:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Facing a loaded gun, you'd be amazed
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.28,0:52:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,how fast you're going to make that shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.35,0:52:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you can make it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.83,0:52:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're facing a loaded gun
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.83,0:52:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,means that you are able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.83,0:52:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.82,0:52:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't that you can't,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.82,0:52:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it's that you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.62,0:52:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.62,0:52:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That changes the whole problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.62,0:52:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to an I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.62,0:52:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I look at why I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.62,0:52:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings me up to the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.62,0:52:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of the juice I'm getting out of it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.62,0:52:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and whether I'm willing to let go of that juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.10,0:52:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I willing to let go of the juice of being right?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.10,0:52:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't get away with the excuse
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.57,0:52:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.82,0:53:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can say to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.82,0:53:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I won't fall into I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.62,0:53:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone says, well, I can't let go of I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.65,0:53:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let go of I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.65,0:53:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you won't let go of I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.81,0:53:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let go of I want, I can't, I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.65,0:53:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.80,0:53:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,At the bottom of all these things
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.80,0:53:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is the willingness to surrender it to God
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.05,0:53:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrender it to the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.05,0:53:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, as a miracle, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.08,0:53:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So humility then removes a lot of the blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.88,0:53:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a reluctance,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.88,0:53:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a rigidity due to the reluctance to learn,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.88,0:53:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn and progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.88,0:53:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We would like to hang on to this homeostasis,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.36,0:53:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,seeming stability,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.45,0:53:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than to shift and feel temporarily off balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.45,0:54:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We like comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.09,0:54:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When you enter the new arena,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.09,0:54:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel unfamiliar.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.25,0:54:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, people will stick in very destructive pathways
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.25,0:54:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because just to change it a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.25,0:54:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,requires some effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.43,0:54:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This one uses the past as an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.62,0:54:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The past justifies being stuck here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.62,0:54:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If you grew up the way I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.62,0:54:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if your mother treated you the way you were,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.62,0:54:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if the Democrats did that to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.62,0:54:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if the Republicans did that to you, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.97,0:54:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the past is justification to stay stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.97,0:54:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you need to see
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.16,0:54:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the present is the change agent,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.32,0:54:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the change agent is the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.32,0:54:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In one second, you can move from heaven to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.32,0:54:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you can move from hell to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.67,0:54:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened from the depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.50,0:55:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened from the depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.33,0:55:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Agonizing, eternal hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.33,0:55:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Far worse than any hell I've ever heard described.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.49,0:55:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell is far, far, far worse than any description
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.49,0:55:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the most greatest imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.75,0:55:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreadful beyond all words.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.32,0:55:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.40,0:55:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus it goes on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.63,0:55:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever. You're in hell forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.26,0:55:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever with no possibility of redemption.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.74,0:55:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. Eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.64,0:55:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, in one second,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.44,0:55:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly, the infinite glory of God shines forth
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.39,0:55:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,from hell to heaven in a tenth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.39,0:55:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.83,0:55:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen, what is it? Zen teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.83,0:55:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This means heaven and hell is exactly one inch.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.76,0:55:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Heaven and hell are very close together.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.76,0:56:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because for some people's ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.76,0:56:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes the extremes of hell before it will let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.76,0:56:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point of blaming the degree of suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.81,0:56:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that occurs in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.81,0:56:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if that's what it takes to let go,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.80,0:56:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then that's what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.80,0:56:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Self, with a capital S, couldn't care less.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.12,0:56:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Will throw you right over a cliff
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.12,0:56:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's what it takes to wake you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.12,0:56:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't wake up and you fall through,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.70,0:56:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but you wake up fast when you hit the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.70,0:56:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite a jolt.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.70,0:56:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.63,0:56:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, blaming things on the past is an excuse
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.84,0:56:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because the present is forever a change agent
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.84,0:56:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the constant asking God for intervention.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.84,0:56:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the pits of hell, there was not even mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.84,0:56:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, at the highest level,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.91,0:56:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's nonlinear and timeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.91,0:56:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonverbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.16,0:57:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor is there any, not a single,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.00,0:57:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,nor is there any, not a self there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.54,0:57:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In hell, there was a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.54,0:57:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.24,0:57:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.33,0:57:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But every instant is also what seems like
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.33,0:57:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the worst of the agony
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.00,0:57:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is the open door to transcending it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.00,0:57:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're never trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.00,0:57:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're never actually trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.00,0:57:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The potentiality is there every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.48,0:57:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that silent agony,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.48,0:57:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a voice arose from somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.95,0:57:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,within the consciousness field
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.24,0:57:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and it said,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.59,0:57:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God, I ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.71,0:57:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.24,0:57:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it only took 35 years
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.24,0:57:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to recover from the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.24,0:57:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of what happened after that tenth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.24,0:58:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the mind was struck silent and dumb
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.37,0:58:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and replaced by a presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.72,0:58:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the presence that speaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.72,0:58:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It uses intellect and the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.45,0:58:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as a tool of expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.45,0:58:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the presence that speaks,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.45,0:58:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,utilizing that which is available
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.77,0:58:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to express itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.80,0:58:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So the past, no matter how bad it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.80,0:58:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is no excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.80,0:58:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because even from the very pits of hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.80,0:58:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've never heard of anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.80,0:58:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who's been lower than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.83,0:58:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,even from the very extreme pits of hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.98,0:58:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,salvation is an instant away.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.98,0:58:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Instant away. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.59,0:58:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.59,0:58:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.39,0:58:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We can let go of the past as an excuse
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.39,0:58:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's not a permanent thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.39,0:58:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the whole idea of past, future and present
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.39,0:58:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are all illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.39,0:58:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no past, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.77,0:58:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing is you can say
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.77,0:58:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have the willpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.93,0:59:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And we just said before,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.93,0:59:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't a matter of willpower, it's willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.12,0:59:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, willpower as conceived of
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.12,0:59:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in ordinary consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.12,0:59:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is force.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.16,0:59:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Force yourself to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.16,0:59:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's grit your teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.96,0:59:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a white knuckler.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.96,0:59:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And willpower is about as strong
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.96,0:59:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as your level of consciousness at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.34,0:59:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's tried willpower to overcome anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.34,0:59:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,like even chewing gum,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.34,0:59:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,will realize how weak it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.34,0:59:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the last stick I'm going to chew, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.27,0:59:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because willpower is only as strong as
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.27,0:59:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,your level of consciousness at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.27,0:59:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever your calibrated level of consciousness is,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.46,0:59:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the strength of your willpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.26,0:59:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the strength of your personal will.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.36,0:59:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, to surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.36,0:59:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and to invoke divine will,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.09,0:59:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we realized that we were powerless
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.09,0:59:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrendered to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.09,0:59:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you invoke divine will
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.09,1:00:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and divine will calibrates at 850.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.09,1:00:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine will at 850
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.09,1:00:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is capable of the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.19,1:00:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at 850, what seems to you impossible
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.19,1:00:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.54,1:00:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At 850, it's a foof.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.38,1:00:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At 855, it's going to be a life-long struggle.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.05,1:00:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Even at 220, it's a life-long struggle.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.17,1:00:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What you by yourself cannot accomplish,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.17,1:00:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly I'll tell you, you can't,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.17,1:00:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because you haven't got what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.74,1:00:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,By surrender to God, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.83,1:00:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you summon forth,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.05,1:00:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you create the opening for divine will,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.05,1:00:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which at 850 will overcome anything in this domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.47,1:00:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 850.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.76,1:00:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No will power.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.76,1:00:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you got no will power.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.85,1:01:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had will power,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.97,1:01:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be calling upon will power.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.97,1:01:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You would have solved it already.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.97,1:01:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that true?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.55,1:01:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't pull up will power.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.41,1:01:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have dissolved already.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.41,1:01:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the personal will doesn't have it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.08,1:01:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from force.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.08,1:01:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's below 200 usually.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.08,1:01:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, divine will at 850.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.11,1:01:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing about will power
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.32,1:01:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it's an illusion
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.32,1:01:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is not the willingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.32,1:01:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The denial, therefore.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.09,1:01:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need will power to do something,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.09,1:01:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that you lack the willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.09,1:01:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you had had the willingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.09,1:01:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have already transcended it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.09,1:01:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wouldn't be requiring will power.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.09,1:01:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.09,1:01:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Paradoxical.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.68,1:01:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says, well, I've been trying to.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.68,1:02:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.48,1:02:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the denial of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.64,1:02:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The denial of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.64,1:02:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really meant that,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.67,1:02:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be done already, would it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.67,1:02:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to try.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.24,1:02:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, S taught that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.24,1:02:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, S would never let you get away with a try.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.31,1:02:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Try was a no-no word in S.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.31,1:02:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Either do it or shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.31,1:02:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,See, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.31,1:02:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is a lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.31,1:02:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And this just puts it off tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.53,1:02:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the reality is to do it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.33,1:02:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's more comfortable to procrastinate
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.62,1:02:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because the fear is of failure.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.65,1:02:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear is if I tackle that,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.65,1:02:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to get over that degree of selfishness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.65,1:02:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to get over this particular addiction,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.65,1:02:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to get over this proclivity,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.65,1:02:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't be able to do it and I'll fail.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.65,1:02:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, underlying the fear of failure
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.65,1:02:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is pride, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.75,1:02:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you do fail?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.42,1:02:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you fail, fail, try, try again.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.42,1:03:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that what they say? Try, try again.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.42,1:03:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Try, try again.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.42,1:03:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so here the temptation is to procrastinate
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.41,1:03:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,out of a fear of failure.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.41,1:03:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If I really face that and try to do it, I might fail.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.41,1:03:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here people pretend
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.67,1:03:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and here the power you need is to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.67,1:03:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a rigorous inner spiritual inventory,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.32,1:03:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,moral inventory then,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.32,1:03:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is very rewarding
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.96,1:03:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as you approach it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.96,1:03:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,with a kind uncle kind of a conscience.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.19,1:03:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind uncle comes from the fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.22,1:03:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You folks have been here in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.25,1:03:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you all beat up.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.25,1:03:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been brainwashed with BS
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.25,1:03:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from the moment you got here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.25,1:03:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I respect the fact that you are not trying
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.25,1:03:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to get out of it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.25,1:03:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and be honest with yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.25,1:03:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, being honest then invokes,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.25,1:04:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when you surrender your own will to God,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.25,1:04:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you then invoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.25,1:04:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,See, God is infinitely
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.25,1:04:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.24,1:04:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Guarantees complete freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.32,1:04:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In my understanding,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.58,1:04:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,God does not intervene unless asked.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.58,1:04:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.00,1:04:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.76,1:04:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you think he knocks you around
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.76,1:04:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and enforces you against your will?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.82,1:04:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would there be divine justice?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.36,1:04:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine justice is that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.36,1:04:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody paddles your canoe except you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.36,1:04:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, nobody deserves the reward
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.36,1:04:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or the consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.36,1:04:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,except yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.36,1:04:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's solely by your own inner judgment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.16,1:04:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.03,1:04:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to say that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.60,1:04:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite justice of God
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.60,1:04:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is absolute and perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.60,1:04:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The justice of God
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.60,1:04:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is innate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.60,1:04:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.60,1:04:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the depictions of God
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.60,1:04:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which are anthropomorphic
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.60,1:05:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and come from primitive cultures,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.86,1:05:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, is that the gods are angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.86,1:05:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you've got this judgmental God
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.05,1:05:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,who's going to punish you for your errors.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.05,1:05:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're created by God,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.85,1:05:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then you were created this way
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.85,1:05:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a propensity to errors.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.85,1:05:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is God going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.85,1:05:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Punch you around because of what he created?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.85,1:05:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the views of a primitive God
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.57,1:05:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,are anthropomorphic, say.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.57,1:05:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They come out of the culture
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.57,1:05:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in which volcanoes are due to angry gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.70,1:05:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Earthquakes are due to angry gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.70,1:05:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Drowsiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.70,1:05:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always these angry gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.69,1:05:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I know how to justify angry gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.69,1:05:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You rip the hearts out of young maidens
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.69,1:05:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,by the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.69,1:05:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.49,1:05:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I think in Mayan culture you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.49,1:05:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the high priest would sometimes rip out
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.49,1:05:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the heart of a thousand a day.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.75,1:05:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A thousand a day with a obsidian knife
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.75,1:05:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,while their hearts are still beating
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.75,1:05:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and throw it down the steps of the Mayan.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.75,1:06:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Pyramids were running with blood,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.26,1:06:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly trying to appease the angry gods
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.39,1:06:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which was in Freud's unconscious, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.39,1:06:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, Freud recognized that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.39,1:06:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, he rejected divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.39,1:06:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He should have just rejected
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.19,1:06:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the false depictions of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.19,1:06:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But the primitive ideas of God
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.19,1:06:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,are what lead to fear of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.19,1:06:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear, fear of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.35,1:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.37,1:06:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we give up pretense and we're honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.37,1:06:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We give up unwillingness and resistance
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.76,1:06:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and we move into acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.76,1:06:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we stop?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.91,1:06:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.94,1:06:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Fine. Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.00,1:06:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.26,1:06:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, do we have any more slides?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.96,1:06:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.45,1:06:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we do it all?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.58,1:06:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God. Isn't that fantastic?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.58,1:07:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.37,1:07:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear God, I went through all the slides.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.37,1:07:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.14,1:07:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.06,1:07:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the obligation is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.06,1:07:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and present a way of contextualization.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.06,1:07:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, contextualization then
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.06,1:07:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,facilitates transcendence of these levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.06,1:07:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're correctly contextualized,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.86,1:07:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,they're relatively easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.86,1:07:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Relatively easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.86,1:07:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.86,1:07:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Relatively easy to transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.92,1:07:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know what the key concepts are.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.32,1:07:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what the key concepts are.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.40,1:07:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Committing your life to devotion to God
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.40,1:07:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be a servant of God
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.46,1:07:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to constantly ask for God's will
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.56,1:07:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,then brings to your side
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.56,1:07:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a great deal of power,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.00,1:07:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,not force,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.93,1:07:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,not ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.93,1:08:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which is trained to white-knuckle it,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.93,1:08:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but actual power.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.44,1:08:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does this power do?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.44,1:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't do it for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.64,1:08:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates a context
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.64,1:08:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in which your...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.37,1:08:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in which your intention is now empowered.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.53,1:08:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say in a weak intentional field
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.53,1:08:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.73,1:08:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have much of an impact.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.88,1:08:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in the name of an infinitely powerful field,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.68,1:08:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,now that decision has enormous power.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.68,1:08:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Enormous power.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.68,1:08:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.68,1:08:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To do it in the name of God then
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.68,1:08:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,empowers the decision,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.68,1:08:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.68,1:08:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So the limitation of the Heisenberg principle,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.78,1:08:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it says,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.78,1:08:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the introduction of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.39,1:08:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,collapses the way it functions.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.39,1:08:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.39,1:08:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't talk about the calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.39,1:08:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the consciousness of the observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.39,1:08:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.32,1:09:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It just, it's an academic mathematical extraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.32,1:09:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intention of a person
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.99,1:09:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of a relatively low level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.37,1:09:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,may have a feeble,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.37,1:09:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,may have a feeble effect on the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.40,1:09:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The same decision by a person
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.40,1:09:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of strict alignment
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.40,1:09:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,may have a powerful impact on the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.40,1:09:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.40,1:09:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Powerful impact on the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.82,1:09:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.85,1:09:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg principle,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.11,1:09:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,then we could even recontextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.11,1:09:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.11,1:09:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When does the Schrodinger potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.11,1:09:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.11,1:09:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,eventuate as the Dirac collapse
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.33,1:09:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of the wave function expression
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.33,1:09:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in the new state of the universe?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.33,1:09:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We could add,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.33,1:09:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it depends on the power of the observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.33,1:09:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.43,1:09:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.43,1:09:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it from clinical experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.56,1:09:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.94,1:09:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.94,1:09:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.20,1:09:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,100% correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.20,1:09:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.20,1:10:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Tally.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.43,1:10:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.27,1:10:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was the clinical observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.94,1:10:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.94,1:10:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a huge practice,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.94,1:10:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,50 employees,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.94,1:10:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,couple floors,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.94,1:10:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple labs,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.94,1:10:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,neurological labs,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.94,1:10:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,EEG labs,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.94,1:10:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, all kinds.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.94,1:10:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a giant practice
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.94,1:10:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had a lot of therapists.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.16,1:10:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I noticed that some clinicians
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.16,1:10:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly got good results
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.19,1:10:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and others pathetically didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.19,1:10:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't have anything to do with academic credentials.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.28,1:10:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.44,1:10:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was saying this morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.44,1:10:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a difference between academic science
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.44,1:10:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and clinical science.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.54,1:10:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.54,1:10:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the credentials were all academic.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.54,1:10:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But I noticed that certain therapists
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.92,1:10:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,consistently got, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.92,1:10:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,great results
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.92,1:10:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and others didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.92,1:10:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, of course, at the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.56,1:11:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know about calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.69,1:11:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you're seeing is the consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.69,1:11:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's a difference between
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.49,1:11:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the academic treater and a healer.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.16,1:11:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The real function of the physician is to heal, to heal.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.26,1:11:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Academic medicine,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.26,1:11:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the way it's become today,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.26,1:11:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is sort of, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.64,1:11:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,pharmacologic mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.74,1:11:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely dehumanized.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.74,1:11:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The medical journals I get now,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.74,1:11:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,there are no humans involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.74,1:11:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no humans.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.74,1:11:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing, no characteristics of humanness at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.94,1:11:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.57,1:11:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Compassion, that's unscientific.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.57,1:11:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention, that's unscientific.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.21,1:11:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd think they're talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.62,1:11:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,abstract principles
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.62,1:11:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,having nothing to do with humanity suffering humanness
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.62,1:11:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or anything like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.62,1:11:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Next to the real.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.62,1:12:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.62,1:12:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are providers of services.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.81,1:12:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not doctors anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.81,1:12:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They're providers of services.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.81,1:12:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a customer.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.46,1:12:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have a practice, you have a locality.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.66,1:12:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this locality,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.86,1:12:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the provider of services to the customer,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.26,1:12:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,like sacks of potatoes, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.26,1:12:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Like they were hardware, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.45,1:12:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardware.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.45,1:12:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We dropped off the screen for repair
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.45,1:12:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the repairman repaired it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.16,1:12:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So I discovered that it was the healing capacity of the clinician
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.54,1:12:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because I could get recoveries with placebos
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.54,1:12:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and academically trained physicians
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.54,1:12:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't get them with active psychopharmacologic agents.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.05,1:12:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How high was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.69,1:12:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we discovered that the power of the observer,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.69,1:12:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the clinician,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.24,1:12:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,had a greater effect on the outcome
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.65,1:13:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,than the scientific principles
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.29,1:13:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of the pharmaceuticals involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.86,1:13:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible to get better recovery from depression
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.86,1:13:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,with a placebo with a very powerful physician
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.86,1:13:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,who really loves the hell out of his patients
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.86,1:13:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and just uplifts them.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.38,1:13:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.30,1:13:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than the tax clinician who calibrates at 202
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.50,1:13:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,who gives them Prozac, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.85,1:13:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So the classic.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.85,1:13:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The physician was supposed to be the healer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.68,1:13:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The healer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.68,1:13:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to heal the patient, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.68,1:13:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not supposed to be the local provider of services.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.68,1:13:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody gets well with a provider of services.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.03,1:13:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,MD online.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.03,1:13:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that big website?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.03,1:13:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,MD online or?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.03,1:13:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,WebMD.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.16,1:13:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.96,1:13:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that tell you?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.51,1:13:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,200.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.05,1:13:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want a physician to treat me at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.47,1:13:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll give me the right bandage.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.79,1:13:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to get well.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.79,1:13:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting well is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.79,1:14:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.82,1:14:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.82,1:14:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means there's other agendas.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.95,1:14:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly 200 denotes lack of humanity,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.95,1:14:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,love, caringness, benevolence,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.95,1:14:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things that really count in the long run.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.13,1:14:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The consequence of a scientific investigation, research,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.50,1:14:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which I've mentioned, I think, before in other lectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.22,1:14:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,From the research, you can calibrate the research design.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.02,1:14:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can calibrate the level of consciousness of the researcher.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.02,1:14:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can tell you the result already.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.02,1:14:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Save yourself $10 million.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.62,1:14:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Save the state of California and Euclid, 10 million,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.62,1:14:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because I can tell you right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.48,1:14:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, and we said it before, Crick's experiment,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.48,1:14:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,discovery of the double helix, calibrated at 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.48,1:14:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,His last experiment, which was to prove that consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.48,1:14:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is solely a product of the physical neuronal activity of the brain,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.68,1:14:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated about 140.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.64,1:15:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the neuronal activity of the brain
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.24,1:15:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is the consequence of consciousness in life, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.51,1:15:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the application, then, of the science of truth, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.68,1:15:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is very valuable in many ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.75,1:15:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention of the devotee is what empowers the information
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.49,1:15:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to become transformative.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.49,1:15:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just hearing the information, and it's not just intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.00,1:15:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but you put the two together.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.36,1:15:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the will, the power of the dedication.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.36,1:15:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So devotion, you see, is powerful because it's not coming from the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.36,1:15:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion is of the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.52,1:15:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the heart is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.64,1:15:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the intellect is limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.64,1:15:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It stops at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.03,1:15:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, just deciding you're going to do something
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.03,1:15:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's reasonable and makes sense,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.03,1:15:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectually obvious, isn't enough to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.95,1:16:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In vocation, I ask Almighty God,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.59,1:16:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,through His Son, Lord Jesus Christ and the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.59,1:16:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to be at my side as I try to overcome this limitation,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.92,1:16:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,which is consequent to being a human.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.53,1:16:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That is powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.33,1:16:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the way to an evolved state is by the power of the devotion,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.25,1:16:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the uncommitted, unreserving devotion
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.25,1:16:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to whatever it takes is whatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.25,1:16:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes is whatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.33,1:16:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes is whatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.23,1:16:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't necessary to go to the depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.06,1:16:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.06,1:17:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eternal agony is not required.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.02,1:17:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just one way.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.37,1:17:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what this ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.60,1:17:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it took for this ego to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.11,1:17:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because it wasn't, the ego had somehow escaped.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.91,1:17:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was pretty ferocious, ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.04,1:17:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It would take you through death without a thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.26,1:17:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,take you to the depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.86,1:17:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And there, in eternal agony of eternal hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.86,1:17:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it finally let go.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.86,1:17:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That should not be necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.04,1:17:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because with the advancement of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.04,1:17:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the information we have available now,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.04,1:17:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,teachers available, recontextualization of the field,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.13,1:17:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualization of the pathway,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.93,1:17:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it should never, it should not ever be necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.93,1:17:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach such an extreme depth of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.93,1:17:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.48,1:17:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Gloria in excelsis Deo.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.48,1:18:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll take a break now
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.21,1:18:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll reconvene in a little while.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.21,1:18:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.21,1:18:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to leave more time for questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.21,1:18:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because I don't want to hurry through them
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.21,1:18:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't want people waiting forever
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.21,1:18:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and not getting tended to.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.21,1:18:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like being in McDonald's, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.21,1:18:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these people are waiting for a cheeseburger.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.01,1:18:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the pressure of all the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.01,1:18:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're going to spend more and more time
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.01,1:18:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,with questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.01,1:18:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can all be who we are with each other
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.01,1:18:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and, you know, as a very compassionate group,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.01,1:18:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, this group calibrates extremely high,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.01,1:18:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and their intention is very strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.04,1:18:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power of the intention of the teacher,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.04,1:18:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the student, and the group
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.04,1:18:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is at maximum opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.04,1:18:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In this setting, a powerful teacher,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.04,1:18:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a powerful student, and a powerful group,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.04,1:18:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the impossible becomes a snap.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.04,1:18:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll see you again in a little while.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.04,1:18:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do questions and answers, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.00,1:19:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, glory to God in the highest.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.28,1:19:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Bless you all.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.28,1:19:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the recess bell?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.60,1:19:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is. Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.66,1:19:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Children, children, recess is over.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.92,1:19:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We're getting ready to start the question and answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.92,1:19:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.56,1:19:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Questions on this side of the room.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.56,1:19:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Book signing on this side.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.56,1:19:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I need my jacket.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.56,1:19:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.56,1:19:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in my left inside jacket pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.84,1:19:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to leave a little more time
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.84,1:19:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.84,1:19:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The feedback we've gotten is that people really enjoy them,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.09,1:19:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, because it's not, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.09,1:19:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualized in a formal kind of a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.09,1:19:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's spontaneous, real.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.64,1:19:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And with Dr. Kalmbach, we were just reviewing
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.76,1:19:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that the power of the intention of a student,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.76,1:20:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or devoted students like this group here,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.76,1:20:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the individual,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.76,1:20:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the group intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.76,1:20:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the intention of the teacher makes it formidable.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.76,1:20:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All three together is about as good as it gets.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.76,1:20:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.12,1:20:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All three together is about as good as it gets.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.12,1:20:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Pow-ee.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.12,1:20:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it while we can.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.47,1:20:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Our being together then is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.53,1:20:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to me, a wonderful experience, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.53,1:20:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the people tell us that the person asking the question
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.72,1:20:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,has to speak closer to the microphone
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.52,1:20:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe a little louder.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.78,1:20:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When they play it back, this voice is too loud
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.78,1:20:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to that voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.78,1:20:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, speak loudly and clearly.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.98,1:20:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can spend a little more time
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.94,1:20:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,answering questions a little more completely
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.94,1:20:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because we don't have such money to ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.94,1:20:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh, I was thinking we didn't have a mic.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.94,1:20:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you hear him all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.58,1:20:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.77,1:21:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because I'm having problems hearing him up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.77,1:21:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Both microphones are turned off.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.62,1:21:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.25,1:21:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I go into tech shock.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.25,1:21:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Tech shock.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.38,1:21:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, you have said in your books or on your tapes
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.76,1:21:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that the kamikaze pilots were calibrating at 390.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.76,1:21:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you compare that to the suicide bombers
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.76,1:21:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you see around the world, do they have the same level
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.02,1:21:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or are they coming from a different...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.02,1:21:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I haven't done that yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.02,1:21:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't tested that?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.98,1:21:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The kamikaze was doing it for the sake of his country
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.11,1:21:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and his leaders, see, and his people.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.11,1:21:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was doing it out of devotion to the emperor
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.55,1:21:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as the representative of God, as representative of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.55,1:22:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what particular bombers are you thinking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.55,1:22:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle East and what you see in Iraq every day.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.55,1:22:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear about suicide bombers.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.55,1:22:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Insurrectionists.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.35,1:22:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Insurrectionist bombings?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.70,1:22:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just start with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.99,1:22:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do the energy level
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.99,1:22:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of insurrectionist bombings resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.99,1:22:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're under 200 resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.34,1:22:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.60,1:22:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be that many of them are just violent people
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.08,1:22:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for an excuse to be violent.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.08,1:22:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're not coming from...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.08,1:22:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to die for a cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.08,1:22:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because they're violent?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.52,1:22:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Insurrectionist bombing is just killing your fellow countrymen
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.52,1:22:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for political power.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.52,1:22:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The bombings are coming because one political party
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.55,1:22:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is trying to dominate another political party.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.55,1:22:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not exactly, you know, devotional.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.55,1:22:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.55,1:23:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be like the Republicans and the Democrats blowing each other up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.55,1:23:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exactly the highest level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.55,1:23:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who say, in that culture, who say they're doing it for God
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.71,1:23:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,are using it as a cover-up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.71,1:23:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.51,1:23:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask what I have in my mind, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.51,1:23:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask what I have in my mind, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.54,1:23:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a form of blasphemy, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.92,1:23:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a violation of the name of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.63,1:23:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it covers extremely low.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.98,1:23:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not really true, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.98,1:23:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.98,1:23:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.56,1:23:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Every verse of the Quran starts out the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.56,1:23:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever read the Quran?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.56,1:23:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.56,1:23:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Every verse says,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.56,1:23:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of Allah, be all merciful.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.76,1:23:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single standard says that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.56,1:23:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of God, be all merciful.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.56,1:23:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You would have to certainly violate.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.68,1:23:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.95,1:24:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, I do feel sorry for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.09,1:24:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.09,1:24:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I think they are misled.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.19,1:24:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the culpability is one thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.92,1:24:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but the accountability is still there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.92,1:24:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.53,1:24:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I listened to the lecture today,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.40,1:24:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wanted to ask about karma
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.57,1:24:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and chronic pain.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.57,1:24:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see the payoff
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.83,1:24:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to the chronic pain in my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.62,1:24:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about the payoff of
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.62,1:24:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,persistent levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.23,1:24:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain things are the consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.23,1:24:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of the karma of humanness.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.55,1:24:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one reason the Buddha said,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.55,1:24:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not identify with the linear
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.55,1:24:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby avoid reincarnation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.90,1:25:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain things are, see,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.70,1:25:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the collective karma of being human.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.43,1:25:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And some prevailing ailments may be specifically karmic.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.78,1:25:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so let's just clarify that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.78,1:25:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Some ailments are merely consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.78,1:25:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to the karmic inheritance of being human.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.16,1:25:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Some expressions represent a specific personal karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.42,1:25:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Such as, I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.48,1:25:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this in front of this group.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.58,1:25:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Some resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.54,1:25:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is personal past karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.22,1:25:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The wrinkles is group.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.22,1:25:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That was good.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.93,1:25:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One's a young handsome swain, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.70,1:25:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so part of it just comes as part of being human.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.70,1:25:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And then some peculiar things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.70,1:25:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,To be born deaf, dumb, and blind.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.70,1:26:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it seems so unique.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.70,1:26:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have these specific karmic propensity there.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.30,1:26:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's served, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.14,1:26:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.94,1:26:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we ask, you know, we ask God to help you endure it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.94,1:26:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and to understand it, to contextualize it,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.94,1:26:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and let go resisting it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.22,1:26:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You can live with pain for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.86,1:26:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been how many years?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.52,1:26:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The pain never goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.65,1:26:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.65,1:26:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what this says on here.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.50,1:26:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These are new books.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.50,1:26:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.50,1:26:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought all of my books.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.50,1:26:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness sakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.50,1:26:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.50,1:26:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also brought something from the minister,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.30,1:26:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from Boulder, in Boulder, Colorado, for you as a gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.30,1:26:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Unity of Boulder?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.30,1:26:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The minister did a series of talks on power versus force recently,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.30,1:26:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wanted you to have those.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.30,1:26:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.30,1:26:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.30,1:26:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we ever speak at Unity of Boulder?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.30,1:26:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.30,1:27:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.30,1:27:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we spoke at the Benedictine Monastery there.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.30,1:27:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you ever come up that way, you're welcome to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.30,1:27:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So my question has to do with people who are in a position of affluence
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.14,1:27:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime who have, you know, the comforts of everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.14,1:27:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,who have unlimited, say, assets to use on the behalf of themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.14,1:27:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and also on the behalf of those around them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.14,1:27:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they go about feeling comfortable, feeling appropriate,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.14,1:27:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and having these things and using them for their own personal use as well
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.14,1:27:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when there's so much, it appears as though there's so much lack and poverty
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.03,1:27:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,all in the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.03,1:27:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, what's the appropriate use of these assets to be a good steward?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.03,1:27:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how they inherit it, karma is karma, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.03,1:27:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it would be the level of consciousness of the person,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.48,1:28:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,how they would best see the fulfillment of the obligation of stewardship
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.48,1:28:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of their assets.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.54,1:28:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, just keeping it in the bank is already serving society.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.12,1:28:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.12,1:28:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Capital itself is necessary for economic survival
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.25,1:28:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the development of the whole civilization.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.25,1:28:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So just leaving it there, if you don't know how to benefit society,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.25,1:28:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the bank will.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.28,1:28:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll loan money to the shoemaker, it'll loan money to, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.28,1:28:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So society benefits, you know, as just a consequence of its being there.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.28,1:28:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The accumulated wealth of a society
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.28,1:28:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically brings benefits to all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.44,1:28:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, the tax base goes up, government gets more wealthy,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.44,1:28:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and humanitarian programs can now be afforded by the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.18,1:29:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Many governments can't afford them because there isn't enough capital in the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.18,1:29:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So capital of its own sake, you know, is not intrinsically non-interiorist, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.97,1:29:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to feel guilty about being a millionaire, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.97,1:29:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell my friends, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.74,1:29:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the further inference of what you're saying, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.82,1:29:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it would be how you see that you might most greatly benefit society.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.82,1:29:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And when wealth reaches a certain level,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.01,1:29:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it begins to exert a moral pressure.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.20,1:29:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see the richest people in America have all evolved great foundations.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.20,1:30:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, in the new book we calibrate the level of consciousness of the major foundations, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.26,1:30:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course they do an enormous amount of good.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.26,1:30:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's true, you can only get so wealthy and then you begin to feel an obligation
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.26,1:30:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to use that wealth for the greatest good, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.46,1:30:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate that, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.94,1:30:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Not out of guilt, but out of seeing it as a responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.94,1:30:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,just like you were saying, what's the responsibility, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.97,1:30:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I didn't feel any guilt when I was poor,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.05,1:30:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,why should I feel guilt when I'm rich, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.10,1:30:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.10,1:30:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's a lady who we quoted her in the book, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.61,1:30:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.61,1:30:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.61,1:30:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for being the great gift to humanity that you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.61,1:30:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You are one of humanity's great teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.61,1:30:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for thinking me worthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.61,1:30:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for helping me to be in your book.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.61,1:30:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.61,1:30:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.61,1:30:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I am supposed to go to Kashmir to complete my new book on Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.61,1:31:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it safe for me to go because it's an insurgency state?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.61,1:31:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you calibrate that?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.61,1:31:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What country are you going?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.61,1:31:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Kashmir.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.61,1:31:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Kashmir in India.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.61,1:31:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kashmir.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.61,1:31:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything going on there now?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.61,1:31:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a Muslim insurgency going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.61,1:31:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.61,1:31:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.61,1:31:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There's Muslims that are bombing things over there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.61,1:31:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with Arizona, sweetheart?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.41,1:31:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I love her dearly and I don't want her...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.02,1:31:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you because the symbols of Jesus in India are not in Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.18,1:31:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you're going there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.18,1:31:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.18,1:31:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.18,1:31:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.56,1:31:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.56,1:31:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Devji is quoted in the book on America.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.56,1:31:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She came from India.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.23,1:31:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The way she contextualized the heart and the essence of America,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.03,1:31:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I quoted to be in contradistinction to the devotees of hate America.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.03,1:31:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.10,1:31:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The hate America comes out of a calibration level of about 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.10,1:32:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And she sees that it's truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.10,1:32:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like some people see these as beautiful, the beauty just stands out.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.10,1:32:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And other people think they should be thrown out, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.10,1:32:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.16,1:32:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She wrote an article in Arizona Republic and I was stunned by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.16,1:32:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I says, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.96,1:32:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is somebody who really gets what the hell it's all about, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.96,1:32:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we wrote for permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.96,1:32:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote her and we got to meet.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.96,1:32:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had to foreshorten it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.96,1:32:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The original article was considerably longer.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.99,1:32:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But for sake of space in the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.99,1:32:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But I tried to get the essence of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.99,1:32:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Although she gave some rather...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.99,1:32:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Because she's also a writer.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.99,1:32:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So she also gave some unique examples of what she was saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.99,1:32:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which I had to delete.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.99,1:32:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.99,1:32:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to ask the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.38,1:32:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The question she holds.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.18,1:32:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.18,1:32:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it's answerable.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.18,1:32:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can answer it as of now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.18,1:32:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.62,1:33:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The area she's holding in mind is currently safe for a person of her extraction
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.62,1:33:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to go into a resistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.20,1:33:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.96,1:33:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She is safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.96,1:33:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The area is safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.96,1:33:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The area that you're holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.96,1:33:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're holding in mind where you're going?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.96,1:33:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.96,1:33:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.76,1:33:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It is currently safe for her.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.43,1:33:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It only says currently.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.75,1:33:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,By tomorrow, maybe...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.75,1:33:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Better call me back before you get on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.42,1:33:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we once were supposed to board a plane to return to Korea.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.42,1:33:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the plane had left.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.90,1:33:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we tried to get on another one.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.42,1:33:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And we used the arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.22,1:33:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the arm said, you're not to go today.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.60,1:33:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is not physically safe to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.71,1:34:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.78,1:34:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's physically not safe to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.78,1:34:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So stop lamenting that you missed the plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.78,1:34:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it just saved your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.78,1:34:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if she wants to know before she gets on the plane,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.78,1:34:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,call us and we'll recalibrate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.54,1:34:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.54,1:34:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.54,1:34:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.54,1:34:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I am from Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.54,1:34:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.54,1:34:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.93,1:34:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.13,1:34:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.13,1:34:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I come from Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.13,1:34:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any suggestions how we might get a better use of your work in there?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.13,1:34:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.29,1:34:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the book has recently been translated into Spanish.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.29,1:34:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.29,1:34:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.29,1:34:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.29,1:34:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.29,1:34:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the first one.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.29,1:34:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.29,1:34:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been invited to speak in Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.29,1:34:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, that's the reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.29,1:34:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But I like going to Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.29,1:34:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I love Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.29,1:34:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.29,1:34:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've never seen people.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.29,1:34:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel very at home there.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.89,1:34:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.09,1:34:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be interested in...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.25,1:34:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I don't speak Spanish, eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.25,1:35:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.25,1:35:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In school, I learned German.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.25,1:35:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I moved out of the German community and haven't used it in all these years.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.25,1:35:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I need to speak Spanish and I only know German, so not too much help.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.25,1:35:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to find a Mexican who understands German and then we can speak in German.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.25,1:35:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.25,1:35:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You got one right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.25,1:35:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.25,1:35:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You could speak English as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.25,1:35:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But would you be interested in participating in...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.05,1:35:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...in an international conference, international congress of spirituality next February?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.25,1:35:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.45,1:35:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to send the details to me in the office.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.45,1:35:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd have to calibrate it and see whether we can or can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.65,1:35:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My own energies are somewhat limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.65,1:35:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, although my heart would like to do many things.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.65,1:35:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.45,1:35:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The physicality doesn't have the energy a lot of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.45,1:35:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.43,1:35:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.63,1:35:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.63,1:35:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.63,1:35:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course I would be delighted with the...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.83,1:35:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.83,1:36:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...the request.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.03,1:36:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand the information.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.23,1:36:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I did, years ago, you know, go through South America.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.43,1:36:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I spoke at the University of Argentina, which I enjoyed a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.63,1:36:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.63,1:36:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.02,1:36:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Stopped off in Brazil and various places.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.37,1:36:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Got to go to Machu Picchu on the way back, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.57,1:36:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, then we ended up in Ecuador.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.32,1:36:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And in those years, it was not a tourist country, South America.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.38,1:36:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There was two planes a week out of Crito, in Ecuador.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.38,1:36:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Two planes a week from Miami, I think it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.58,1:36:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.58,1:36:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I got there for the Wednesday plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.18,1:36:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, the clock had stopped in the middle of the airport, years and years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.38,1:36:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In Ecuador, time doesn't mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.86,1:36:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be there to know what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.26,1:36:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, but it's there tomorrow, next time it was...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.06,1:36:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, the Wednesday plane won't leave till Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.18,1:36:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.98,1:36:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In Ecuador, it doesn't bother you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.78,1:36:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In Chicago, you'd have a fit, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.58,1:37:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecuador, you say, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.58,1:37:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I went back Saturday to catch the plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.38,1:37:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Supposed to leave at 12 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.38,1:37:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Quarter to 12.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.11,1:37:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,At quarter to 12, there's one plane in Ecuador.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.51,1:37:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire airport, one plane sitting out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.91,1:37:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Quarter to 12, I hear its engine stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.22,1:37:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, now what?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.42,1:37:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The Thursday plane doesn't leave till Saturday, and now its engine...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.02,1:37:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, it's siesta time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.02,1:37:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.82,1:37:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's this airplane costing $1,000 an hour, I'm sure, for maintenance, insurance, and God knows.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.24,1:37:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They shut it down for siesta.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.11,1:37:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten minutes to 3, the engine started back up, we got on, and everybody flew out of there at 3 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.91,1:37:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wednesday plane didn't leave till Saturday, and it didn't leave at noon, it left at 3,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.51,1:37:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and it didn't make any difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.74,1:37:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, things are different now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.94,1:37:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I can assure you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.94,1:37:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the invitation, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.34,1:37:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Thank you, doctor, for your great wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.14,1:37:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're serious, you can send it to us at the office,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.34,1:37:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.54,1:37:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes, I'll make sure of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.14,1:38:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much indeed. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.30,1:38:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Your voice has the highest vibration I've ever heard in my life,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.30,1:38:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I just loved it from the moment I heard it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.82,1:38:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I've listened to about 300 hours on audio,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.62,1:38:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is my first time to hear you in person,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.62,1:38:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just rings true to my heart. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.75,1:38:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A year ago, I was driving by Lake Powell,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.35,1:38:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was listening to one of your lectures about you getting rid of your glasses,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.50,1:38:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and after hearing you do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.10,1:38:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I rolled down the window and threw my glasses that I purchased out the window.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.37,1:38:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd bought them less than a week before,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.03,1:38:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I still don't see.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.63,1:38:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen in years, so what?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.50,1:39:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.50,1:39:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I love not seeing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.88,1:39:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very freeing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.48,1:39:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so freeing to take them off.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.68,1:39:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just was open
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.28,1:39:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to any suggestions, coaching, to heal myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.48,1:39:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How long has it been?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.88,1:39:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a year, over a year.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.08,1:39:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.62,1:39:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What I did with it is I kept surrendering,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.59,1:39:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, all of a sudden, of its own,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.83,1:39:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the seeingness returned, at least to a degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.37,1:39:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Up until that time, I couldn't see the edge of the highway,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.77,1:39:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm driving around these mountain roads with a thousand-foot drop-off,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.80,1:39:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the edge of the highway would somehow light up
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.30,1:39:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,only as I needed to see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.10,1:39:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So I got that you only get to see what you need to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.42,1:39:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't get to see what you want to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.82,1:40:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you do is keep surrendering the wantingness to see
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.82,1:40:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the juice you get out of the visual linearity, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.22,1:40:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning, significance, the entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.31,1:40:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, it's almost like a meditative experience
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.11,1:40:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because when you go within the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.11,1:40:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the thoughts are coming by, like the passing scenery,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.31,1:40:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to suck you in to identify with the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.31,1:40:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're really getting a training has nothing to do with vision.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.51,1:40:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with surrendering the experiencer
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.31,1:40:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who's always seeking to juice the visual with novelty, entertainment, titillation, value.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.51,1:40:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So who knows where it might lead?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.58,1:40:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm excited.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.58,1:40:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Constantly surrendering it to divinity, to God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.16,1:40:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.56,1:40:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, interesting experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.76,1:40:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is. May I?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.96,1:40:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.16,1:40:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.36,1:40:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.98,1:40:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.84,1:41:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to see Makananda one time.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.10,1:41:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I really liked Makananda.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.70,1:41:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in the mountains north of, what do they call them, the Catskills.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.26,1:41:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Makananda, I really loved him.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.68,1:41:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the mantra they had was Om Namah Shivaya, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.98,1:41:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then during the lecture, he would wear orange knit hats.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.98,1:41:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And periodically through the lecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.38,1:41:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he had a whole pile of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.18,1:41:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd put it on a hat and then he'd throw it on the audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.38,1:41:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would all rush and grab it, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.58,1:41:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his energy and vibration in that hat, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.38,1:41:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he'd put another hat on.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.18,1:41:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then 20 minutes later, he'd throw another hat on.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.98,1:41:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.07,1:41:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was a delightful person to know, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.50,1:41:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Makananda.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.54,1:41:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Brief knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.83,1:41:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My question has to do with intention and karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.63,1:41:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of my profession, people die as a result of the training
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.30,1:41:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that I provide.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.11,1:42:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I understand that when the two parties meet, it's their karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.91,1:42:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But what karma do I carry when I deal through my training
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.79,1:42:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and providing that training?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.79,1:42:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it like a military, paramilitary?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.39,1:42:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Military and police.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.39,1:42:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.56,1:42:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're fulfilling with integrity the requirements of the office?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.04,1:42:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.04,1:42:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To be the enforcer of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.50,1:42:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Protectors of society.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.90,1:42:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The law in our population.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.66,1:42:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want me to calibrate the intention?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.57,1:42:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to be what the level is.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.78,1:42:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of how the karma is affected?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.18,1:42:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah, because your intention is what makes it, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.98,1:42:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So if your intention is to fulfill, you know, during war,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.98,1:42:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you're forced to kill somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.34,1:42:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't, you're going to get shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.94,1:42:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the honor of your country and the fulfillment of your obligation,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.02,1:43:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you have this role to fulfill.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.82,1:43:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's got to fulfill this role.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.62,1:43:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's got to fulfill the role.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.26,1:43:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It also may be a transitory.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.06,1:43:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it's served its purpose, you'll move on to something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.48,1:43:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But it might be the momentary requirement of your own karmic volition.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.34,1:43:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.93,1:43:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The volition comes from them, what they do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.33,1:43:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because when we calibrated guns, we were amazed it was 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.56,1:43:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A gun is neutral.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.92,1:43:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a saber or a dagger.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.92,1:43:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What you do with the dagger, you know, but the knife,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.92,1:43:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a knife calibrates at 200, so is a gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.46,1:43:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're a teacher of what is needed to maintain law and order.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.46,1:43:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And law and order, without law and order, society can't exist, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.71,1:43:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're fulfilling a role in the need of society, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.81,1:44:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And if your intention is to fulfill that need, as integrous as you can, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.58,1:44:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think the role itself is one way or the other, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.58,1:44:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can understand your concern or question about it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.12,1:44:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.12,1:44:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that was World War II, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.12,1:44:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question was in front of every participant in World War II at all times.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.41,1:44:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what's the spiritual, you know, of this?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.41,1:44:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mines and blowing people up and 20 caliber and guns, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.21,1:44:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Bombers flying at you, kamikaze.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.53,1:44:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And you swing back 20 millimeter calibers.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.53,1:44:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, am I killing him or am I protecting my shipmates?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.91,1:44:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,20 caliber, you know, anti-aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.70,1:45:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You swing back in that thing like this and take her right out of the air.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.56,1:45:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy just went up in pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.59,1:45:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,With either that or my shipmates going up in pieces, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.90,1:45:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Press the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.90,1:45:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're on the line, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.90,1:45:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's really pulling up is the courage to fulfill that obligation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.92,1:45:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think once that's fulfilled, I don't think you have to do it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.92,1:45:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you transcend that and you're done with that karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.23,1:45:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the karma of the officers, the karma of the soldiers that I trained.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.23,1:45:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.23,1:45:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're fulfilling your obligation to God and country.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.23,1:45:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I see, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.68,1:45:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that would be the oath you take.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.68,1:45:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
